WEBVTT

00:00:00.320 --> 00:00:05.120
Hi, my name is Ryan Johnson and I'm a Data Science Advisor here at Posit,

00:00:05.120 --> 00:00:12.160
and I'm excited to host our first ever Posit Team Community Demo on April 26th,

00:00:12.160 --> 00:00:17.440
and we'll continue this series of demos on the last Wednesday of every month going forward.

00:00:18.080 --> 00:00:23.040
Now during these demos, we'll walk through an end-to-end data science workflow using

00:00:23.040 --> 00:00:28.799
our three professional data science tools that make up Posit Team. We have Posit Workbench,

00:00:28.799 --> 00:00:34.880
Posit Connect, and Posit Package Manager. Now most importantly, these events are open to the

00:00:34.880 --> 00:00:40.880
entire data science community. Now you may ask yourself, like, why would I want to attend these

00:00:40.880 --> 00:00:46.400
Posit Team demos? So here are a few reasons why I believe these sessions will be valuable

00:00:46.400 --> 00:00:50.400
not just to Posit customers, but also the greater data science community.

00:00:51.119 --> 00:00:56.880
So first off, maybe you've never heard of Posit Team before. Either you're new to a company that

00:00:56.880 --> 00:01:01.840
uses Posit Team or you're just exploring options for your team's analytics platforms.

00:01:02.400 --> 00:01:08.239
So during these demos, we'll make sure to provide a high-level overview of Posit Team and also

00:01:08.239 --> 00:01:14.400
highlight some of the newest features we've added to our tool chain. Now secondly, maybe you do use

00:01:14.400 --> 00:01:20.000
Posit Team today and you're looking to expand your data science capabilities. For example, is your

00:01:20.000 --> 00:01:24.879
team thinking about using Python more? Maybe creating some Dash applications or hosting your

00:01:24.879 --> 00:01:31.120
first API? Every month, we'll keep things fresh and discuss a new topic and touch upon the various

00:01:31.120 --> 00:01:38.639
capabilities within Posit Team. And finally, this is a great time to ask us at Posit any questions

00:01:38.639 --> 00:01:43.040
you have about Posit Team. During this demo, we'll be hanging out in the chat to answer

00:01:43.040 --> 00:01:48.320
any and all of your questions you have about Posit Team workflows, capabilities, licensing,

00:01:48.320 --> 00:01:53.680
and more. We hope these demos are valuable to you and the data science team, and we look forward

00:01:53.680 --> 00:01:59.279
to seeing you there.

